fix: eliminate command injection in review-mode approve/cancel

Replace shell-interpolated commands in approve_current and
cancel_approve_current with safe argument passing.

- approve_current: pass path as a positional argument to sh -c
  ("echo APPROVED > \"$1\"") instead of interpolating into the
  command string
- cancel_approve_current: use ["rm", "-f", &path] directly,
  bypassing the shell entirely

Previously, task_id and subtask.name (sourced from filesystem reads)
were interpolated into sh -c command strings, allowing a crafted
directory name with shell metacharacters to execute arbitrary commands.
